Your Questions About "Session End":
When is "session end"?
YES, exactly! "Session end" means:

When you see "Session too long" - That's the main trigger
When you're about to close Kiro - Even if no warning
When you're taking a break - If stepping away for a while
When you finish a major task - Good stopping point
How to do the "Manual updates - Semantic context":
Option 1: Use the new hook (EASIEST)

update-context
# or: bash .kiro/hooks/update-context.sh
It will prompt you with 4 questions:

What did you accomplish?
What problem did you solve?
What's the current status?
What needs to be done next?
Option 2: Manual (if you prefer) Open .kiro/session-state/context-summary.md and add at the bottom:

## Session Update: 2025-11-17 22:00

### What Was Accomplished
[Describe what you did]

### Problem Solved
[What issue was fixed]

### Current Status
[What's working, what's not]

### Next Steps
[What to do next session]
